<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/4512881-sherri-hayes"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1482440976i/4512881._UX100_CR0,25,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/4512881-sherri-hayes">Sherri Hayes</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Unfortunately, no. My publisher decided against producing the audio book for Trust, which means I would have to have it produced myself. They were nic<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Unfortunately, no. My publisher decided against producing the audio book for Trust, which means I would have to have it produced myself. They were nice enough to give me all the information regarding the first three so that the fourth book would be consistent with the same narrators, etc., however, to produce it would cost $12,000 and I don't have that kind of money. I've started a Gofundme page to try and help raise the funds needed, but at this point its a long way off from becoming a reality. <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.gofundme.com/findinganna">http://www.gofundme.com/findinganna</a><a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
