    <a title="Andrea (mrsaubergine)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4036326-andrea-mrsaubergine"><img alt="Andrea (mrsaubergine)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1279773012p2/4036326.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/748682608?book_show_action=true">Oct 24, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Andrea (mrsaubergine)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Andrea (mrsaubergine)" href="/user/show/4036326-andrea-mrsaubergine">Andrea (mrsaubergine)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4036326-andrea-mrsaubergine?shelf=my-edits">my-edits</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer748682608" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8638161856075408907">Fabulous end to the series. I don&apos;t want to give too much away, but it&apos;s a joy to see Brianna&apos;s journey, and her progress from the first book. Stephan is always wonderful and here we see how much she supports him, as well as the other way around. Mysteries are solved, comeuppances gained, and conflicts abated. Loved it. Well done, Sherri Hayes!</span>
  <span id="freeText8638161856075408907" style="display:none">Fabulous end to the series. I don't want to give too much away, but it's a joy to see Brianna's journey, and her progress from the first book. Stephan is always wonderful and here we see how much she supports him, as well as the other way around. Mysteries are solved, comeuppances gained, and conflicts abated. Loved it. Well done, Sherri Hayes!</span>
  <a data-text-id="8638161856075408907" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


